<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900615-0029</DOCNO><DOCID>900615-0029.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Consolidated Natural Gas Co.:   Investment of $48 Million   In Storage Sites Is Planned</HL><DATE>06/15/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   CNG</CO><LP>   Consolidated Natural Gas Co., Pittsburgh, said it plans toinvest $48 million in underground natural-gas storagefacilities, following approval of the plan by the FederalEnergy Regulatory Commission.   Consolidated, a large producer, transporter anddistributor of natural gas, said it will equip depleted gaswells to store sufficient gas for six retail gas distributorsto provide 38 million cubic feet of gas daily during peak useperiods beginning in 1991. Additional storage is to beprovided four of the companies in 1992, adding capacity for41 million cubic feet of gas daily. The retail distributorswould own the gas.</LP><TEXT>   The project also will provide 20 million cubic feet dailyof storage service for Texas Eastern Transmission Corp. in1992, the company said.</TEXT></DOC>